mother's body anymore.

00:21:59.600 --> 00:22:01.760 align:middle line:90%
Now we must overregulate it.

00:22:01.760 --> 00:22:03.470 align:middle line:90%
We must put it into rules.

00:22:03.470 --> 00:22:04.973 align:middle line:90%
We must say, oh, no, no, no.

00:22:04.973 --> 00:22:06.140 align:middle line:90%
You must follow these rules.

00:22:06.140 --> 00:22:08.303 align:middle line:90%
You must do it this way.

00:22:08.303 --> 00:22:10.220 align:middle line:84%
Whatever happened to the
trusting of the body?

00:22:10.220 --> 00:22:24.520 align:middle line:90%


00:22:24.520 --> 00:22:26.920 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:22:26.920 --> 00:23:59.550 align:middle line:90%


00:23:59.550 --> 00:24:02.230 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:24:02.230 --> 00:24:35.307 align:middle line:90%


00:24:35.307 --> 00:24:38.560 align:middle line:84%
>> So with my first
two were natural.

00:24:38.560 --> 00:24:40.310 align:middle line:84%
On birth date, I knew
they were coming.

00:24:40.310 --> 00:24:41.110 align:middle line:90%
They came.

00:24:41.110 --> 00:24:41.993 align:middle line:90%
They were wonderful.

00:24:41.993 --> 00:24:44.410 align:middle line:84%
And then I thought that was
going to happen with my third,

00:24:44.410 --> 00:24:47.860 align:middle line:84%
especially even faster, like
it was just going to spit out.

00:24:47.860 --> 00:24:50.783 align:middle line:90%
She was actually a week late.

00:24:50.783 --> 00:24:51.700 align:middle line:90%
They wanted to induce.

00:24:51.700 --> 00:24:53.590 align:middle line:90%
I said, no, we're going to wait.

00:24:53.590 --> 00:24:55.960 align:middle line:84%
Finally, I started
having some contractions.

00:24:55.960 --> 00:24:57.910 align:middle line:90%
I said, amazing, let's go.

00:24:57.910 --> 00:25:00.490 align:middle line:84%
And there were a lot of
women waiting in the triage

00:25:00.490 --> 00:25:02.650 align:middle line:84%
before they sent us
to labor and delivery.

00:25:02.650 --> 00:25:05.230 align:middle line:84%
They were bad, my
contractions, but not terrible.

00:25:05.230 --> 00:25:07.030 align:middle line:84%
And then a doctor
came in and said,

00:25:07.030 --> 00:25:08.960 align:middle line:84%
do you want to get
up there faster?

00:25:08.960 --> 00:25:10.700 align:middle line:90%
And I said, well, I don't know.

00:25:10.700 --> 00:25:11.590 align:middle line:90%
Sure.

00:25:11.590 --> 00:25:14.350 align:middle line:84%
And she said, well,
if I break your water,

00:25:14.350 --> 00:25:16.060 align:middle line:84%
then they're going
to send you up there,

00:25:16.060 --> 00:25:18.010 align:middle line:84%
but just don't tell any
of the other doctors

00:25:18.010 --> 00:25:20.950 align:middle line:84%
that I broke your water, and
it didn't break naturally.

00:25:20.950 --> 00:25:23.520 align:middle line:90%


00:25:23.520 --> 00:25:24.960 align:middle line:90%
>> So I arrived at the hospital.

00:25:24.960 --> 00:25:26.702 align:middle line:84%
I was expecting the
midwives to be there,

00:25:26.702 --> 00:25:27.660 align:middle line:90%
and they weren't there.

00:25:27.660 --> 00:25:31.030 align:middle line:84%
And then they took me
to the operating room.

00:25:31.030 --> 00:25:34.450 align:middle line:84%
>> So she stuck her
hand in to her elbow.

00:25:34.450 --> 00:25:35.250 align:middle line:90%
>> Her hand?

00:25:35.250 --> 00:25:41.460 align:middle line:84%
>> Her hand to her elbow, and
with her nail broke the water.

00:25:41.460 --> 00:25:45.070 align:middle line:84%
She takes her hand out,
and my water has broken.

00:25:45.070 --> 00:25:47.190 align:middle line:84%
I'm having terrible
contractions now.

00:25:47.190 --> 00:25:49.137 align:middle line:84%
They take me to the
labor and delivery.

00:25:49.137 --> 00:25:50.220 align:middle line:90%
They give me the epidural.

00:25:50.220 --> 00:25:51.430 align:middle line:90%
I'm feeling better.

00:25:51.430 --> 00:25:52.230 align:middle line:90%
I called everyone.

00:25:52.230 --> 00:25:53.940 align:middle line:84%
I'm feeling happy,
and my baby's coming.

00:25:53.940 --> 00:25:55.200 align:middle line:90%
Everything's good.

00:25:55.200 --> 00:25:57.210 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden,
I have people

00:25:57.210 --> 00:25:59.400 align:middle line:84%
coming to me with oxygen
masks and feeling me.

00:25:59.400 --> 00:26:03.597 align:middle line:84%
I had about 20 people
in the little room.

00:26:03.597 --> 00:26:05.930 align:middle line:84%
>> And then all of a sudden
I felt like I was surrounded

00:26:05.930 --> 00:26:06.530 align:middle line:90%
by nurses.

00:26:06.530 --> 00:26:08.510 align:middle line:84%
And they were all saying lie
down, lie down now, lie down

00:26:08.510 --> 00:26:09.310 align:middle line:90%
now.

00:26:09.310 --> 00:26:11.242 align:middle line:90%
And I didn't know why.

00:26:11.242 --> 00:26:12.200 align:middle line:90%
And I kept saying, why?

00:26:12.200 --> 00:26:12.990 align:middle line:90%
What's going on?

00:26:12.990 --> 00:26:14.865 align:middle line:84%
And then finally they
kind of just guided me.

00:26:14.865 --> 00:26:17.282 align:middle line:84%
And they said, well, your
legs are going to fall asleep.

00:26:17.282 --> 00:26:18.740 align:middle line:84%
You're going to
fall off the table.

00:26:18.740 --> 00:26:20.490 align:middle line:84%
>> And my husband's
like, what's going on?

00:26:20.490 --> 00:26:22.790 align:middle line:84%
They said to my husband
this is emergency C-section.

00:26:22.790 --> 00:26:26.720 align:middle line:84%
She's got about a minute to
live before we take her out.

00:26:26.720 --> 00:26:28.295 align:middle line:90%
Her heart rate is at zero.

00:26:28.295 --> 00:26:31.380 align:middle line:90%


00:26:31.380 --> 00:26:33.820 align:middle line:84%
>> It sort of felt like
an out of body experience.

00:26:33.820 --> 00:26:37.537 align:middle line:84%
I kind of feel like I
emotionally checked out.

00:26:37.537 --> 00:26:39.870 align:middle line:84%
>> I don't know how much
anesthesia they gave me at that

00:26:39.870 --> 00:26:40.670 align:middle line:90%
point.

00:26:40.670 --> 00:26:42.570 align:middle line:84%
So I was knocked
out, but knocked out

00:26:42.570 --> 00:26:44.850 align:middle line:84%
to the point where I
couldn't open my eyes.

00:26:44.850 --> 00:26:47.250 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't feel anything.

00:26:47.250 --> 00:26:51.320 align:middle line:84%
>> I didn't even notice when
they started the surgery.

00:26:51.320 --> 00:26:52.490 align:middle line:90%
>> They take the baby out.

00:26:52.490 --> 00:26:53.390 align:middle line:90%
I had my eyes closed.

00:26:53.390 --> 00:26:54.450 align:middle line:90%
I didn't even know.

00:26:54.450 --> 00:26:58.010 align:middle line:84%
So about six hours
passed, and I was finally

00:26:58.010 --> 00:27:01.460 align:middle line:84%
able to hold her
for the first time.

00:27:01.460 --> 00:27:04.730 align:middle line:84%
>> It almost doesn't feel like
he's your baby because you

00:27:04.730 --> 00:27:07.790 align:middle line:90%
don't feel anything at all.

00:27:07.790 --> 00:27:10.940 align:middle line:84%
And in the wake of that,
I felt like I have a baby,

00:27:10.940 --> 00:27:13.790 align:middle line:84%
but I never gave
birth to a baby.

00:27:13.790 --> 00:27:17.480 align:middle line:84%
And that's a bit of
a sadness with me.

00:27:17.480 --> 00:27:19.490 align:middle line:84%
>> What I found
out later was that,

00:27:19.490 --> 00:27:23.990 align:middle line:84%
by breaking my water early,
she went into the birth canal,

00:27:23.990 --> 00:27:26.180 align:middle line:84%
but there was no water
left, and she got stuck.

00:27:26.180 --> 00:27:28.970 align:middle line:90%
And her heart rate stopped.

00:27:28.970 --> 00:27:33.830 align:middle line:84%
>> I do feel like I was robbed
of the experience of having

00:27:33.830 --> 00:27:34.760 align:middle line:90%
my baby.

00:27:34.760 --> 00:27:39.490 align:middle line:84%
I spent nine months carrying
him and never gave birth.

00:27:39.490 --> 00:27:42.165 align:middle line:84%
>> It's all because they wanted
to keep everybody moving.

00:27:42.165 --> 00:27:43.040 align:middle line:90%
>> Move things along.

00:27:43.040 --> 00:27:46.060 align:middle line:84%
>> Move things along quicker
instead of let nature take its

00:27:46.060 --> 00:27:48.700 align:middle line:90%
course.

00:27:48.700 --> 00:29:10.120 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:29:10.120 --> 00:29:14.790 align:middle line:84%
>> So these are gifts that
I received in the mail from

00:29:14.790 --> 00:29:21.900 align:middle line:84%
the formula companies,
Nestle and Enfamil.

00:29:21.900 --> 00:29:24.090 align:middle line:84%
And I actually know my
friends have received things

00:29:24.090 --> 00:29:25.370 align:middle line:90%
from Similac, as well.

00:29:25.370 --> 00:29:26.170 align:middle line:90%
I have not.

00:29:26.170 --> 00:29:30.346 align:middle line:90%


00:29:30.346 --> 00:29:36.030 align:middle line:84%
Just bottles, and
formula, and coupons.

00:29:36.030 --> 00:29:39.225 align:middle line:84%
I received a diaper bag
from Nestle, as well.

00:29:39.225 --> 00:29:48.800 align:middle line:90%


00:29:48.800 --> 00:29:51.780 align:middle line:90%
The Enfamil I was not expecting.

00:29:51.780 --> 00:29:54.870 align:middle line:84%
It actually arrived
after the baby was born,

00:29:54.870 --> 00:29:57.630 align:middle line:84%
and I'm not too
sure exactly where

00:29:57.630 --> 00:29:59.497 align:middle line:90%
they got my information from.

00:29:59.497 --> 00:30:01.830 align:middle line:84%
I think it might have been
from a hospital, because this

00:30:01.830 --> 00:30:04.782 align:middle line:84%
is the brand that
the hospital uses.

00:30:04.782 --> 00:30:06.240 align:middle line:84%
I have the measuring
tape that they

00:30:06.240 --> 00:30:08.550 align:middle line:84%
used to do Hunter's
measurements right

00:30:08.550 --> 00:30:10.050 align:middle line:84%
after he was born
where they marked,

00:30:10.050 --> 00:30:12.750 align:middle line:84%
and it's actually
branded Enfamil right

00:30:12.750 --> 00:30:15.720 align:middle line:90%
from the hospital.

00:30:15.720 --> 00:30:20.070 align:middle line:84%
And this bottle I know came
from my prenatal classes

00:30:20.070 --> 00:30:21.120 align:middle line:90%
at the hospital, as well.

00:30:21.120 --> 00:30:23.500 align:middle line:84%
They had them in a basket
for everybody to pick up

00:30:23.500 --> 00:30:24.750 align:middle line:90%
at the beginning of the class.

00:30:24.750 --> 00:30:39.360 align:middle line:90%


00:30:39.360 --> 00:30:43.440 align:middle line:84%
>> In the 1970s, it was so
tragic for mothers who thought

00:30:43.440 --> 00:30:48.060 align:middle line:84%
they were doing the best for
their babies and to see this

00:30:48.060 --> 00:30:51.030 align:middle line:84%
horrendous consequence when
they believed the billboards,

00:30:51.030 --> 00:30:54.410 align:middle line:84%
and the advertising, and
received these free samples.

00:30:54.410 --> 00:30:57.060 align:middle line:84%
And to end up with
a dead baby and have

00:30:57.060 --> 00:31:00.010 align:middle line:84%
to carry their dead
baby home in a cloth,

00:31:00.010 --> 00:31:01.110 align:middle line:90%
it just broke my heart.

00:31:01.110 --> 00:31:23.920 align:middle line:90%


00:31:23.920 --> 00:31:28.090 align:middle line:84%
>> Many years the government
has faced the challenge of child

00:31:28.090 --> 00:31:33.370 align:middle line:84%
mortality, but when it came
to issues of now legislating

00:31:33.370 --> 00:31:36.830 align:middle line:84%
the international code of
breast milk substitutes,

00:31:36.830 --> 00:31:39.355 align:middle line:84%
it was a long and
tedious process.

00:31:39.355 --> 00:31:43.030 align:middle line:90%


00:31:43.030 --> 00:31:47.290 align:middle line:84%
It requires an
advocate, because there

00:31:47.290 --> 00:31:52.130 align:middle line:84%
were a lot of vested interests
from the private sector.

00:31:52.130 --> 00:31:55.300 align:middle line:90%
And they were very resistant--

00:31:55.300 --> 00:31:56.860 align:middle line:90%
extremely resistant.

00:31:56.860 --> 00:31:59.410 align:middle line:90%


00:31:59.410 --> 00:32:02.020 align:middle line:84%
Kenya had a very
unique situation.

00:32:02.020 --> 00:32:06.070 align:middle line:84%
We had a public health
and sanitation ministry,

00:32:06.070 --> 00:32:09.030 align:middle line:84%
which was charged with
preventive actions

00:32:09.030 --> 00:32:12.475 align:middle line:84%
towards reduction
of child mortality.

00:32:12.475 --> 00:32:15.940 align:middle line:90%


00:32:15.940 --> 00:32:19.660 align:middle line:84%
When you look at the health
budgets, a huge chunk of this

00:32:19.660 --> 00:32:23.860 align:middle line:90%
is spent on corrective services.

00:32:23.860 --> 00:32:25.510 align:middle line:90%
What is it that we are treating?

00:32:25.510 --> 00:32:27.310 align:middle line:90%
What is it that we are curing?

00:32:27.310 --> 00:32:35.470 align:middle line:84%
Many of them are diseases
that are easily preventable.

00:32:35.470 --> 00:32:40.300 align:middle line:84%
We quoted that exclusive
breastfeeding can actually

00:32:40.300 --> 00:32:45.700 align:middle line:84%
contribute to 13% reduction
in infant mortality.

00:32:45.700 --> 00:32:59.242 align:middle line:90%


00:32:59.242 --> 00:33:04.910 align:middle line:84%
To do all this, the
investment sounds enormous,

00:33:04.910 --> 00:33:06.110 align:middle line:90%
looks enormous.

00:33:06.110 --> 00:33:08.780 align:middle line:90%
Indeed, it is enormous.

00:33:08.780 --> 00:33:15.990 align:middle line:84%
If you want to go it alone,
it may be almost not doable,

00:33:15.990 --> 00:33:22.050 align:middle line:84%
but it is through partnerships
and through integration,

00:33:22.050 --> 00:33:27.820 align:middle line:84%
both into the media and into
high profile legislators.

00:33:27.820 --> 00:33:33.000 align:middle line:84%
So the government is fully
committed to educating.

00:33:33.000 --> 00:33:36.800 align:middle line:84%
We are in discussion with Kenya
Association of Manufacturers

00:33:36.800 --> 00:33:41.330 align:middle line:84%
to create awareness with the
marketers and the producers

00:33:41.330 --> 00:33:44.450 align:middle line:84%
of infant formula
on what they can do,

00:33:44.450 --> 00:33:47.270 align:middle line:84%
and what they cannot do,
and what are the penalties

00:33:47.270 --> 00:33:48.485 align:middle line:90%
at their own cost.

00:33:48.485 --> 00:33:51.120 align:middle line:90%


00:33:51.120 --> 00:33:53.710 align:middle line:84%
>> There are governments
globally that have done very

00:33:53.710 --> 00:33:57.100 align:middle line:84%
good work in addressing the
marketing and have legislated

00:33:57.100 --> 00:34:00.760 align:middle line:84%
how companies are permitted to
market the product and label

00:34:00.760 --> 00:34:03.040 align:middle line:84%
their product in
their jurisdictions.

00:34:03.040 --> 00:34:06.100 align:middle line:84%
Nevertheless, there are
other countries, particularly

00:34:06.100 --> 00:34:09.620 align:middle line:84%
producer countries,
such as the US, Canada,

00:34:09.620 --> 00:34:12.850 align:middle line:84%
some of the European countries,
where the products are being

00:34:12.850 --> 00:34:15.489 align:middle line:84%
produced, and where there
is a very strong lobby

00:34:15.489 --> 00:34:19.480 align:middle line:84%
to protect the industry from
these types of marketing

00:34:19.480 --> 00:34:21.219 align:middle line:84%
regulations, because,
of course, it

00:34:21.219 --> 00:34:24.580 align:middle line:84%
would impede their ability
to label and promote

00:34:24.580 --> 00:34:25.679 align:middle line:90%
as they see fit.

00:34:25.679 --> 00:34:29.400 align:middle line:90%


00:34:29.400 --> 00:34:30.530 align:middle line:90%
>> It's a huge industry.

00:34:30.530 --> 00:34:34.880 align:middle line:84%
They are lobbying for hospitals
to give out their gift packages

00:34:34.880 --> 00:34:38.330 align:middle line:84%
and information, and to doctors
to recommend their products.

00:34:38.330 --> 00:34:40.969 align:middle line:84%
You're not getting a gift
basket with a breast pump

00:34:40.969 --> 00:34:43.630 align:middle line:84%
or with supportive advice
on how to breastfeed.

00:34:43.630 --> 00:34:47.449 align:middle line:84%
They're getting it on how
to get on the formula.

00:34:47.449 --> 00:34:49.280 align:middle line:84%
World Health
Organization came out

00:34:49.280 --> 00:34:52.130 align:middle line:84%
with guidelines that were
adopted by many countries,

00:34:52.130 --> 00:34:54.440 align:middle line:84%
and many countries
implemented it,

00:34:54.440 --> 00:34:57.350 align:middle line:90%
but the United States did not.

00:34:57.350 --> 00:35:00.270 align:middle line:84%
Marketing is a huge business
and our great country,

00:35:00.270 --> 00:35:03.170 align:middle line:84%
and I believe there is
an economic incentive

00:35:03.170 --> 00:35:05.210 align:middle line:84%
to discourage women
from breastfeeding.

00:35:05.210 --> 00:35:07.670 align:middle line:84%
That whole industry
makes a lot of money

00:35:07.670 --> 00:35:11.290 align:middle line:84%
off of having packaged milk,
as opposed to breastfeeding,

00:35:11.290 --> 00:35:13.700 align:middle line:84%
and the governmental
policies supported

00:35:13.700 --> 00:35:16.550 align:middle line:84%
their economic interests,
not the health interests

00:35:16.550 --> 00:35:17.820 align:middle line:90%
of the mother and the child.

00:35:17.820 --> 00:35:22.570 align:middle line:90%


00:35:22.570 --> 00:35:27.760 align:middle line:84%
>> The Philippines imports $500
million US yearly of baby milk

00:35:27.760 --> 00:35:30.610 align:middle line:90%
products.

00:35:30.610 --> 00:35:34.420 align:middle line:84%
And the milk companies here in
the Philippines every year--

00:35:34.420 --> 00:35:39.430 align:middle line:84%
they rake $1 billion
sales every year.

00:35:39.430 --> 00:35:42.370 align:middle line:84%
And that comes from the
pocket of the poor women who

00:35:42.370 --> 00:35:45.250 align:middle line:90%
have more children.

00:35:45.250 --> 00:35:46.600 align:middle line:90%
It's a big issue.

00:35:46.600 --> 00:35:51.550 align:middle line:84%
It's marketing by the milk
companies of just one product--

00:35:51.550 --> 00:35:56.080 align:middle line:84%
important product, but
glamorized through advertising.

00:35:56.080 --> 00:35:59.770 align:middle line:84%
They will be the politicians
to endorse the product

00:35:59.770 --> 00:36:05.350 align:middle line:84%
through television, through
radio, magazines, billboards,

00:36:05.350 --> 00:36:08.360 align:middle line:90%
even through text messages.

00:36:08.360 --> 00:36:12.950 align:middle line:84%
There is no mercy with
advertising of milk products.

00:36:12.950 --> 00:36:16.010 align:middle line:84%
They entice the
government officials.

00:36:16.010 --> 00:36:19.220 align:middle line:84%
They entice the lawmakers
to break the law

00:36:19.220 --> 00:36:21.500 align:middle line:90%
and weaken the milk code.

00:36:21.500 --> 00:36:24.310 align:middle line:84%
>> I think there's this
misconception that somehow

00:36:24.310 --> 00:36:27.800 align:middle line:84%
Nestle has reformed, and the
other companies have pulled up

00:36:27.800 --> 00:36:29.820 align:middle line:84%
their socks and
become responsible.

00:36:29.820 --> 00:36:31.730 align:middle line:84%
But if we look at
the statistics that

00:36:31.730 --> 00:36:36.500 align:middle line:84%
are being put out by UNICEF and
by the WHO, it's still huge.

00:36:36.500 --> 00:36:38.540 align:middle line:84%
It's still well over
a million deaths

00:36:38.540 --> 00:36:42.490 align:middle line:84%
related to not breastfeeding
globally every year.

00:36:42.490 --> 00:36:45.950 align:middle line:84%
And when we think of how many
years this has been going,

00:36:45.950 --> 00:36:48.650 align:middle line:84%
and how many years the
international code of marketing

00:36:48.650 --> 00:36:53.620 align:middle line:84%
of breast milk substitutes
has been in place since 1981,

00:36:53.620 --> 00:36:56.330 align:middle line:84%
and inappropriate
marketing still continues--

00:36:56.330 --> 00:36:58.220 align:middle line:84%
and we still have
to struggle trying

00:36:58.220 --> 00:37:01.970 align:middle line:84%
to implement these provisions
to protect breastfeeding.

00:37:01.970 --> 00:37:04.820 align:middle line:84%
And then you add up all the
years and all the deaths,

